Date:  15/1/2003
Source:  Capital Times
Author:
Vol / Page:  6
Edition:
Quote:  Karetu grass, or flax saturated witrh scented oils like raukawa, taramea gum, kopuru (fragrant moss) and tarata (lemonwood), were used as grass belts and head bands by Maori. Karetu was important in aiding conception, courtship and Maori ceremonies.
